Today I explored the Bettercap tool in Linux.

This is one of the most powerful tools I’ve seen so far for network analysis and penetration testing.

I learned that Bettercap can:

Discover devices on a network
Monitor traffic
Capture packets
Perform Man-in-the-Middle testing

One thing that really interested me was how much information can be seen inside a local network.

This tool also showed me why using secure networks and encrypted connections is very important.

At first, the commands looked difficult, but after practicing a little, the workflow became easier to understand.

Still learning networking and cybersecurity step by step 🔐
